    "_postman_id": "mbankingcore-api-complete",
    "name": "MBankingCore API Complete Collection",
    "description": "Complete API testing collection for MBankingCore with full endpoint coverage.\n\n## Features:\n- 🏦 Banking Authentication (2-step OTP process)\n- 📱 Device session management\n- 🔄 Automated token refresh\n- ✅ Complete API coverage (44 endpoints)\n- 💰 Multi-account banking support\n- 📝 Article management (CRUD)\n- 🎯 Onboarding content management\n- 📸 Photo gallery management\n- ⚙️ Config management system\n- 📋 Terms & Conditions management\n- 🔐 Privacy Policy management\n- 👥 User management (Admin)\n- 🏛️ Owner-level operations\n- 🧪 Complete testing scenarios\n\n## API Coverage (44 endpoints):\n- **Public APIs** (7 endpoints)\n  - Health Check (1)\n  - Terms & Conditions (2)\n  - Privacy Policy (2)\n  - Onboarding (2)\n- **Banking Authentication APIs** (3 endpoints)\n- **Protected User APIs** (18 endpoints)\n  - User Profile (3)\n  - Session Management (3)\n  - Bank Account Management (5)\n  - Article Management (5)\n  - Photo Management (4)\n  - Configuration (1)\n- **Admin Management APIs** (14 endpoints)\n  - Article Management (1)\n  - Onboarding Management (3)\n  - Photo Management (1)\n  - User Management (4)\n  - Configuration Management (3)\n  - Terms & Conditions (1)\n  - Privacy Policy (1)\n- **Owner Management APIs** (2 endpoints)\n  - User Creation & Updates (2)\n\n## Testing Order:\n1. **Public APIs** - No authentication required\n2. **Banking Authentication** - 2-step login process\n3. **Protected APIs** - User profile, sessions, bank accounts, content\n4. **Admin APIs** - Content and user management\n5. **Owner APIs** - Advanced user role management\n\n## Usage:\n1. Import environment file: `MBankingCore-API.postman_environment.json`\n2. **Important**: Update `banking_account_number` to a unique value before testing\n3. Run collection with automated token handling\n4. Test all API endpoints systematically\n\n## Banking Authentication Flow:\n1. Banking Login → Submit credentials and get login_token + OTP\n2. Banking Verify → Submit login_token + OTP and get session tokens\n3. Access protected endpoints → Auto token refresh\n4. Test CRUD operations on bank accounts and other resources\n5. Logout selectively → Per device or all devices\n\n## Important Notes:\n⚠️ **Account Numbers Must Be Unique**: Each account number must be unique across the system. If testing with existing data, ensure you use a unique account number in the environment variables to avoid database constraint violations.\n\n🔑 **Environment Variables**: The collection uses pre-configured variables for testing. Update these values as needed:\n- `banking_account_number`: Use unique 16-digit number\n- `banking_phone`: Use unique phone number\n- `banking_name`: Full name (8+ characters)\n- `banking_mother_name`: Mother's name (8+ characters)\n- `banking_pin_atm`: 6-digit PIN",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
